wikipedia_page.main: Dominic James Chambers (born 6 January 1984) is former English professional cricketer. He played one first-class cricket match for Kent County Cricket Club during the 2006 season, and remained a squad member for 2007. He was born in Canterbury in Kent.Chambers made 11 Second XI appearances for Kent's Second XI in 2003 before making his first-class debut against Cambridge UCCE in May 2006 at Fenner's. He made two final appearances for the Second XI in 2008. In local cricket he played for Folkestone, St Lawrence and Highland and Canterbury Cricket Clubs in the Kent Cricket League.
